entries.definition:
r–j–ʿ to return, to turn back, to recur, to revert; to take back, to
claim back; to back down, to reply, to give back, to resume an
activity; to become emaciated. Of this root, eight forms occur 107
times in the Qur’an: رَجَعَ rajaʿa 35 times; أَرْجَعَ ʾarjaʿa 11 times;
رُجِّعَ rujjiʿa 36 times; يَتَرَاجَعَ yatarājaʿa once; رَجْع rajʿ three times;

349

